---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Résumé"
  description="Joao V. Rocha — AV engineer + full-stack developer. Sound Image (Clair Global), Suitsupply SF, Vocal Livre, Rock in Rio. Latin Grammy nominee."
  channel="03"
  channelLabel="RÉSUMÉ"
  channelColor="yellow"
>
  <section class="container">
    <header class="resume-hero">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--yellow">CH 03 · ROUTE</p>
      <h1>Joao V. Rocha.</h1>
      <p class="contact">
        SAN FRANCISCO, CA · <a href="mailto:joaovorocha@gmail.com">joaovorocha@gmail.com</a> ·
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/victordorocha/">LINKEDIN</a> ·
        <a href="https://github.com/joaovorocha">GITHUB</a>
      </p>
      <p class="print-hint">Tip: <kbd>⌘P</kbd> to save a clean PDF.</p>
    </header>
  </section>

  <article class="resume-body">

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <p>
    AV engineer and full-stack developer with 10+ years behind a live audio
    console and a Node + Postgres operations platform running in production
    today. Latin Grammy nominee (2023, <em>Temporal</em>), Rock in Rio
    alumnus, currently on the Sound Image / Clair Global SF Bay crew for
    clients including Apple and Dolby. The kind of operator who builds the
    tool when the tool doesn't exist yet.
  </p>

  <h2>Selected experience</h2>

  <h3>AV Engineer · Sound Image (Clair Global)</h3>
  <p class="meta">Nov 2025 – present · San Francisco Bay Area · Part-time / on-site</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Load-in, cabling, rigging, and operation of professional audio systems for high-end corporate productions including Apple and Dolby.</li>
    <li>PA tuning, system optimization, and wireless frequency coordination on Shure Axient Digital / PSM rigs.</li>
    <li>FOH and monitor on Yamaha CL5; Dante-networked signal flow end-to-end.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Audio Engineer · Clair Global · Block Inc. conference</h3>
  <p class="meta">Oct 2025 · Oakland, CA · Seasonal</p>
  <ul>
    <li>One of 10 engineers deploying city-wide audio infrastructure — fiber-optic backbone with decentralized speaker systems across a multi-stage corporate event.</li>
    <li>Sole engineer on Stage 16 from load-in through show — system setup, rigging, cabling, live operation.</li>
    <li>PA tuning and real-time RF coordination shared across the campus.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Stock Manager &amp; Internal Tools Developer · Suitsupply</h3>
  <p class="meta">Feb 2024 – Mar 2026 · San Francisco, CA · Full-time</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Built and shipped the <a href="/projects/daily-ops-platform">Daily Operations Platform</a> from scratch — Node + Express, PostgreSQL 15, Redis, WebSockets, PWA. <strong>50+ daily users, sub-200 ms response times</strong>, replaced paper-based stockroom workflows.</li>
    <li>Real-time integrations with Salesforce, PredictSpring, UPS, and Gmail (OAuth 2.0 + Google Cloud Pub/Sub). MCP servers for inventory, shipments, and radio operations.</li>
    <li>Linux / PM2 / Nginx deploy with smart routing that auto-flips clients between local WiFi and Tailscale based on network conditions.</li>
    <li>Ran daily stockroom operations and a warehouse team in parallel with the engineering work.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>A1 Audio Engineer / OPS Coordinator · Vocal Livre</h3>
  <p class="meta">Jun 2015 – Dec 2022 · São Paulo, Brazil · Full-time</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Lead audio engineer and technical producer across an entire band's touring and broadcast operation — <strong>events from 100 to 25,000 attendees</strong>, touring lead across Brazil.</li>
    <li>FOH and monitor mixes; opener of the <em>Por Toda Terra</em> tour at Brasília; technical advance, rider negotiation, freight, run-of-show, crew scheduling.</li>
    <li><strong>Latin Grammy Nominee 2023</strong> — production team on the album <em>Temporal</em>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>A2 · Rock in Rio</h3>
  <p class="meta">Sep 2017 · Rio de Janeiro, Brazil · Seasonal</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Supported senior techs on RF coordination and stage audio across a month-long run — <strong>80,000 attendees per day</strong>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>AV Operations · UNASP (Centro Universitário Adventista)</h3>
  <p class="meta">Jan 2015 – Dec 2020 · São Paulo, Brazil · Full-time</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Led AV operations for <strong>5,000+ weekly attendees</strong> — audio, video, lighting, broadcast.</li>
    <li>Trained students on signal flow, console operation, and broadcast workflow.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>IT Support Analyst · Colégio Adventista IABC</h3>
  <p class="meta">2012 – 2014 · Goiás, Brazil</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Technical support for 200+ faculty and staff — networking, AV, hardware, remote support.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Selected projects</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/projects/shaddow"><strong>Shaddow</strong></a> — 12 V automotive dock platform built around a Mac. Front Dock (current board): 4-layer USB / power / dual-CAN extender with USB-C PD 45 W and an ESP32-S3 control plane. KiCad + Flux.ai, going to JLCPCB fab.</li>
    <li><a href="/projects/daily-ops-platform"><strong>Daily Operations Platform</strong></a> — Node + Postgres + WebSockets PWA. 50+ daily users in production at Suitsupply SF.</li>
    <li><a href="/projects/live-audio"><strong>Live audio</strong></a> — a decade of FOH, monitor, and RF across festivals, tours, and corporate productions.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Skills</h2>
  <div class="skills-grid">
    <div class="skill-col">
      <h4>Live audio</h4>
      <p><strong>Consoles</strong> — Yamaha CL5 / QL / PM5D, DiGiCo SD / S, Avid S6L, Allen &amp; Heath dLive / iLive.</p>
      <p><strong>PA</strong> — Meyer Sound (PANTHER, LEO, MILO, Leopard), L-Acoustics (K1, K2, Kara), d&amp;b audiotechnik (J, V, Y).</p>
      <p><strong>RF / IEM</strong> — Shure Axient Digital, Shure PSM, Sennheiser EW, Wireless Workbench.</p>
      <p><strong>Networking</strong> — Dante, NDI, Crestron, BlackMagic, OBS, Wirecast.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-col">
      <h4>Software</h4>
      <p><strong>Backend</strong> — Node, Express, PostgreSQL, Redis, WebSockets, REST, OAuth 2.0.</p>
      <p><strong>Platform</strong> — PWAs, MCP servers, Google Cloud Pub/Sub, Gmail / Salesforce / UPS APIs.</p>
      <p><strong>Infra</strong> — Linux, PM2, Nginx, SSL / Let's Encrypt, Tailscale.</p>
      <p><strong>Other</strong> — React Native, Pro Tools, python-can.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-col">
      <h4>Hardware</h4>
      <p><strong>EDA</strong> — KiCad 8, Flux.ai, JLCPCB fab packs.</p>
      <p><strong>Design</strong> — 12 V automotive power, USB-C PD, multi-rail buck/boost, galvanic isolation.</p>
      <p><strong>Buses</strong> — USB 2.0 hubs, dual CAN / FDCAN (listen-only), OBD-II, SLCAN.</p>
      <p><strong>MCU</strong> — STM32G0, ESP32-S3, INA226 monitoring, BTS7008 PROFET.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="skill-col">
      <h4>Operations &amp; languages</h4>
      <p><strong>Ops</strong> — Warehouse management, RFID, Salesforce, PredictSpring, run-of-show, crew scheduling, rider negotiation.</p>
      <p><strong>Languages</strong> — English &amp; Portuguese (native / bilingual). Spanish (elementary).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Certifications &amp; education</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Allen &amp; Heath dLive Certification — May 2026</li>
    <li>Dante Level 1 (3rd Edition) — Audinate, Apr 2026</li>
    <li>Shure Axient Digital / PSM</li>
    <li>Networking for Audio Professionals</li>
    <li>B.A. Communication (Radio &amp; Television Broadcasting Technology), UNASP São Paulo — 2020</li>
  </ul>

  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .resume-hero {
    margin: 3rem 0 var(--chapter);
    max-width: 32ch;
  }
  .resume-hero h1 {
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1.25rem;
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 6vw, var(--fs-h1, 4rem));
    line-height: 1.05;
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
  }
  .resume-hero .contact {
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-micro);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-micro);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--console-dim);
    margin: 0;
    overflow-wrap: anywhere;
  }
  .resume-hero .contact a { color: var(--cap-cyan); }
  .resume-hero .print-hint {
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-micro);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-micro);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--console-dim);
    margin: 0.75rem 0 0;
  }
  .resume-hero .print-hint kbd {
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid var(--console-rule);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 0 0.35em;
    color: var(--cap-yellow);
  }
  .resume-body {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 2rem 4rem;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .resume-body h2 { margin-top: 4rem; color: var(--cap-yellow); }
  .resume-body h3 { margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
  .resume-body h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: var(--fs-micro);
    letter-spacing: var(--tr-micro);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--cap-yellow);
  }
  .resume-body .meta {
    color: var(--console-dim);
    font-family: var(--f-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }

  .skills-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem 2rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .skill-col p { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.45; }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .resume-hero { max-width: 100%; }
    .resume-hero h1 { font-size: clamp(2rem, 9vw, 3rem); }
    .resume-body {
      padding: 0 1.25rem 3rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    .resume-body h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
    .resume-body a { overflow-wrap: anywhere; word-break: break-word; }
    .skills-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 380px) {
    .resume-hero h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .resume-body { font-size: 0.95rem; }
  }

  /* Print stylesheet — clean black-on-white, hide nav/footer/console chrome */
  @media print {
    :global(html), :global(body) {
      background: #fff !important;
      color: #000 !important;
    }
    :global(.site-header),
    :global(header.site-header),
    :global(.site-footer),
    :global(footer),
    :global(.channel-rail),
    :global(nav) {
      display: none !important;
    }
    :global(.container) { padding: 0 !important; max-width: 100% !important; }

    @page {
      margin: 0.55in 0.6in;
      size: Letter;
    }

    .resume-hero {
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
      max-width: 100%;
    }
    .resume-hero .eyebrow,
    .resume-hero .print-hint { display: none !important; }
    .resume-hero h1 {
      font-size: 22pt;
      margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
      color: #000 !important;
    }
    .resume-hero .contact {
      color: #000 !important;
      font-size: 9pt;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }
    .resume-hero .contact a {
      color: #000 !important;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .resume-body {
      max-width: 100% !important;
      margin: 0 !important;
      padding: 0 !important;
      font-size: 9.5pt;
      line-height: 1.32;
      color: #000 !important;
    }
    .resume-body h2 {
      margin-top: 0.85rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
      font-size: 11pt;
      color: #000 !important;
      border-bottom: 1px solid #000;
      padding-bottom: 0.1rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .resume-body h3 {
      font-size: 10pt;
      margin: 0.55rem 0 0.1rem;
      color: #000 !important;
    }
    .resume-body h4 {
      color: #000 !important;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
    }
    .resume-body .meta {
      color: #000 !important;
      font-size: 8pt;
      margin: 0 0 0.3rem;
    }
    .resume-body p { margin: 0 0 0.4rem; }
    .resume-body ul {
      margin: 0.1rem 0 0.5rem 1rem;
      padding: 0;
    }
    .resume-body li {
      margin: 0 0 0.15rem;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }
    .resume-body a {
      color: #000 !important;
      text-decoration: none;
    }
    .resume-body em { font-style: italic; }
    .resume-body strong { font-weight: 600; }

    .skills-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      gap: 0.5rem 1.25rem;
      margin-top: 0.3rem;
    }
    .skill-col p {
      font-size: 8.75pt;
      line-height: 1.3;
      margin: 0 0 0.2rem;
    }

    h3, h4 { page-break-after: avoid; }
    ul, p { page-break-inside: avoid; }
  }
</style>
